      <h1>About Hugo</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A little context on the person behind this blog and the themes that
        shape the writing here.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I write about AI, technology, learning, and the systems that shape how
        people and organizations grow. After earning a PhD in Engineering from
        Stanford, my career has taken me through product and technology
        leadership roles at <a href="https://about.udemy.com/press-releases/udemy-appoints-hugo-sarrazin-as-chief-executive-officer/">Udemy</a>,
        UKG, and McKinsey, where I helped build McKinsey Digital Labs. I
        started this blog as a place to reflect more openly on product
        strategy, workforce transformation, and the practical impact of AI on
        how we learn, work, and build.
      </p>
    </div>
